# Environmental Combat

The battlefield is never just an empty room. Rain turns cobblestones slick. Fire spreads from overturned lanterns. Chandeliers hang overhead waiting to be cut loose. Barrels provide cover but might contain alchemical reagents. Every fight happens somewhere, and that somewhere matters.

Environmental combat transforms static battlefields into dynamic tactical puzzles. Smart combatants use terrain for advantage, create hazards to control enemies, and exploit elevation for tactical superiority. The environment isn't just scenery—it's a weapon, a shield, and a challenge all at once.

